+## 211 Service Partner Pilot Reference
+
+The WALLET-210 staging pilot is the end-to-end operator demo for a 211 service
+partner. It must run against the deployed `wallet_interface` API/UI backed by
+`ipfs_datasets_py.wallet`, not a browser-only mock. Use synthetic participant
+data and a named staging partner DID.
+
+Pilot UI/API sequence:
+
+1. Create or load the staging wallet through `POST /wallets` and open the Abby
+   UI with `walletApiBaseUrl`, `walletId`, `actorDid`, and the appropriate key
+   parameters.
+2. In `Uploads`, add a document and save a precise location. The UI sends the
+   document to `/wallets/{wallet_id}/documents` or
+   `/wallets/{wallet_id}/documents/text` and the location to
+   `/wallets/{wallet_id}/locations`. Operators may show record IDs and storage
+   status, but not plaintext coordinates outside the user's own entry form.
+3. Create a purpose-bound partner grant with
+   `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/records/{record_id}/grants`. For the pilot, use a
+   specific partner DID, purpose such as `211_partner_navigation`, the minimum
+   needed abilities, and output caveats such as `redacted_derived_only`.
+4. Open `Recipient access` as the partner and run the redacted analysis action.
+   The UI issues any required invocation through
+   `/records/{record_id}/analysis-invocations` and calls
+   `/records/{record_id}/analyze/redacted`. The partner view must not display
+   emails, phone numbers, SSNs, full document text, or precise coordinates.
+5. Open `Proofs` as the wallet owner and create a `location_region` proof for
+   the saved location. The receipt may show `claim`, `region_id`, verifier
+   metadata, proof hash, and public input names. It must not expose `lat`, `lon`,
+   target coordinates, witness values, or private location payloads.
+6. Register or select an approved analytics template, then use `Group facts` to
+   submit consent and contribute only approved derived fields through
+   `/wallets/{wallet_id}/analytics/contributions`. Contributions should create
+   an `analytics_contribution` proof receipt and an `analytics/contribute` audit
+   event.
+7. Return to `Recipient access` as the owner and revoke the partner grant. A
+   subsequent partner invocation must fail, grant receipts must show `revoked`,
+   and audit must include `grant/revoke`.
+8. Open `Audit` and confirm the timeline includes `record/add`, `grant/create`,
+   `invocation/issue`, `invocation/verify`, `record/analyze_redacted`,
+   `proof/create`, `analytics/consent_create`, `analytics/contribute`, and
+   `grant/revoke`.
+
+The repository-level browser regression for this pilot is
+`wallet_interface/ui/tests/fullstack-wallet.spec.ts`. It starts a live wallet
+API with local encrypted storage, drives the UI workflow above, and asserts the
+same API privacy and audit boundaries used by the third-party blackbox harness.
+
